  >
</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
Research <span>Overview</span>
</h2>

<p>
RNA expression analysis is central to transcriptomics because it measures the dynamic activity of genes rather than the static sequence of DNA. By quantifying RNA levels, researchers can identify active pathways, compare biological states, classify disease subtypes, and understand how cells respond to internal and external signals.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, RNA expression is presented as a foundational layer of transcriptomic discovery: the bridge between genomic information, cellular function, disease biology, biomarker discovery, and multi-omics interpretation.
</p>

</section>

